/*----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 |                                                                            |
 |                             THEMES README                                  |
 |                                                                            |
 |  Update for domus.Link 2.0 - require a file in the top level under the     |
 |     the theme_name to be mobile or web to identify the type to show in     |
 |     the frontend selection list for themes. This file can be empty.        |
 +----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

 Directory structure

 -> theme
	|
	------> theme_name
			|
			----------> theme_type (web | mobile)
			|
			----------> theme_name.css
			|
			----------> images\
			|
			----------> tpl\

	Notes: 
	
	* theme_name (Directory) and theme_name.css must be identical.
	* images directory contains all the images
	* tpl directory contains template files
	* theme_type is a file to identify which theme list the theme should be presented in.